Subject: [PATCH 4/6] fix: memoize CardAttachments with React.memo
 (client-render-perf)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CardAttachments renders inside every card (freeform/grid/stream/
columns) and receives only primitive/null props, so default shallow
equality is correct. Wrapping it in React.memo prevents the
attachment preview subtree from re-rendering on every unrelated
parent state update (drag, selection, modal toggle, etc.).

DraggableCard was considered but skipped: its onPositionChange /
onDelete callbacks are currently per-card closures at the callsite,
so React.memo there would require a broader API change to pass
cardId as an argument — out of scope for the hotfix.

