Subject: [PATCH 5/6] fix: optimistic update for bulk student add instead of
 router.refresh (client-render-perf)

After a teacher bulk-added students, ClassroomDetail called
router.refresh() which re-ran the classroom RSC tree and refetched
both the full student list and the teacher's board memberships from
Postgres before any UI change was visible.

The POST /api/classroom/:id/students handler already returns the
newly created student records. Propagate them through the
AddStudentsModal onAdded callback and merge them into local state
locally, so the table updates instantly and the existing
per-student state (selection, QR thumbnails, etc.) is preserved.

Other classroom mutations (delete, reissue, batch-delete, link /
unlink board) were already optimistic; this closes the remaining
router.refresh path.

